      },
      "date": "2022-11-21 01:09:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI remember Neil pushing a patch like this. If this patch is needed then why can I successfully build ldiskfs with newer kernels? Just curious.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "6168b1e2bf94d7b1747bdd451cc02885b16ec05e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2022-11-21 03:56:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> I remember Neil pushing a patch like this. If this patch is needed then why can I successfully build ldiskfs with newer kernels? Just curious.\n\nI can't... with SLE15-SP4.  Exactly which newer kernels can you build on?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "d0e37ff0efca2aaa86327feb2b48934c8b01f465",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2022-11-21 14:46:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nUbuntu 20 running 5.8, 5.11 and 5.13 kernels.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "caff1411577e288ec8e37919d9f0ca6f554e5ab3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2022-11-22 00:18:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> Ubuntu 20 running 5.8, 5.11 and 5.13 kernels.\n\nStrange.  In each of these kernels EXT4_IGET_SPECIAL is defined, but EXT4_GET_BLOCKS_KEEP_SIZE isn't.\nSo HAVE_LDISKFS_GET_BLOCKS_KEEP_SIZE will be defined.\nCode in osd-ldiskfs/osd_io.c tests #ifndef HAVE_LDISKFS_GET_BLOCK_KEEP_SIZE which fails, so it doesn't even try to compile code that uses LDISKFS_GET_BLOCK_KEEP_SIZE (which is obviously backwards).\nSo you don't get an error.... so why do I get an error?\nAh-ha.  I was building 2.15.1 which doesn't have support for newer kernels so I added some patches including Shaun's \"LU-15543 ldiskfs: Linux kernel 5.14.21 server support\".  This flips the #ifndef to #ifdef.  The #ifndef is \"obviously\" wrong, but now that wrongness doesn't cancel out the wrongness of the testing of EXT4_IGET_SPECIAL when defining HAVE_LDISKFS_GET_BLOCK_KEEP_SIZE.\nSo your kernels build correctly for the wrong reasons - two mistakes effectively cancel each other out.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
